{
  "texts": [
    "Milodowski et al.",
    "84 reports that small scale disturbances less than 2 ha could be underestimated by up to 50%.",
    "Similarly, the Hansen forest loss data in the tropics is reported to have a 13 % false positive rate and a 17 % false negative rate.",
    "In Africa, the lowest accuracy was found in sub-Saharan Africa, with false negatives of up to 48%, indicating an underestimation of forest loss in this region, specifically in dry forests 2.",
    "Thus, care must be taken when interpreting this data."
  ]
}